Section 1:
Act 147 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H2/12/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1315
4
5 By: Representatives Torres, Barnes, Barnett, A. Brown, N. Burkes, Childress, Eaton, Gonzales Worthen,
6 Hall, Henley, McGruder, Nazarenko, Steele
7 By: Senator Dees
8
For An Act To Be Entitled
9
10 AN ACT TO AUTHORIZE A BLOOD TYPE DESIGNATION TO BE
11 PLACED ON A DRIVER'S LICENSE OR IDENTIFICATION CARD;
12 AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO AUTHORIZE A BLOOD TYPE DESIGNATION TO
17 BE PLACED ON A DRIVER'S LICENSE OR
18 IDENTIFICATION CARD.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 27, Chapter 16, Subchapter 8, is
23 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
24 27-16-818. Blood type designation.
25 (a)(1) A person, or the parent or guardian of a person, may apply to
26 the Office of Driver Services to obtain a blood type designation on a
27 driver's license or identification card issued under this subchapter by
28 providing:
29 (A) A signed form stating the blood type of the person;
30 and
31 (B) Payment of the fee for the driver's license or
32 identification card authorized under this chapter.
33 (2) If the person seeks a duplicate or substitute driver's
34 license with the blood type designation and his or her driver's license has
35 not expired, the fee shall be as provided under ยง 27-16-806.
36 (b) The Office of Driver Services may:
*ZRC031*
02-12-2025 10:15:36 ZRC031
As Engrossed: H2/12/25 HB1315
1 (1) Determine the appropriate placement of the blood type
2 designation on a driver's license or identification card authorized under
3 this section; and
4 (2) Promulgate rules for the administration of this section.
5 (c) This section does not require a person other than an applicant
6 under this section to:
7 (1) Provide his or her blood type to the Office of Driver
8 Services; or
9 (2) Have a blood type designation placed on his or her driver's
10 license or identification card.
11 (d) An applicant under this section is exclusively responsible for:
12 (1) The accuracy of information submitted to the Office of
13 Driver Services; and
14 (2) Verification of the accuracy of the information placed on
15 the applicant's driver's license or identification card, including without
16 limitation the obligation to request an immediate correction if the
17 information is incorrect.
18
19 SECTION 2. DO NOT CODIFY. Effective date. This act is effective on
20 and after January 1, 2026.
21
22 /s/Torres
